title: Winter Bird Walk: Bird Away the Winter Blues
text: Description There is nothing like the beautiful color of songbirds in the snow! We will enjoy our winter resident songbirds and ducks, and perhaps a few surprises. February is also when raptors are beginning to find mates, so we will be on the lookout for Peregrine Falcons, hawks, and occasional eagles. Checking registration status. When - Sat, Feb 17, 2024 8:00 am - 9:30 am Who Adults & Families - 14 & up Cost - Adult Members Free - Adult Nonmembers Free - Child Members Free - Child Nonmembers Free Where Location: Magazine Beach Park Nature Center, Cambridge - Questions? Contact us: - [781-259-2220](tel:781-259-2220) [[email protected]](/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#4e232f292f3427202b2c2b2f2d260e232f3d3d2f3b2a3b2c212060213c29) Instructors - Kathy Dia - Field Teacher, Birding Guide Instructions Meet in front of the Nature Center at 668 Memorial Drive in Cambridge, MA. We will travel in a loop around the park, so wear comfortable walking shoes. Parking is available but please avoid driving if possible. Binoculars will be available upon request.
